    <text type="letter">
        <body>
            <opener>
                <dateline>
                    <name type="place">Harper &amp; Brothers' Editorial Rooms.</name>
                    <name type="place">New York,</name>
                    <date when="1884-10-22">Oct. 22, 1884.</date>
                </dateline>
                <salute>Dear Mr. Whitman:</salute>
            </opener>
            <p> Please find enclosed Messrs Harper &amp; Brothers' cheque for thirty dollars in
                payment for your poem Of That Blithe Throat of Thine. And you have the Messrs
                Harpers' permission to use the poem in a collection of your poems six months (or
                later) after our publication.<ptr
                    target="med.00762_n1"/></p>
            <closer>
                <salute>With thanks, sincerely yours,</salute>
                <signed>H. M. Alden.</signed>
                <salute>Editor of Harpers' Magazine.</salute>
            </closer>
        </body>
    </text>
